text: Dichen Lachman (born 22 February 1982) is a Nepalese-born Australian actress and movie producer. She is best known for her roles in the television series Neighbours, Dollhouse, NCIS: Los Angeles, Hawaii Five-0, Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. and CSI: Crime Scene Investigation. She also plays Gemma Scout/Ms. Casey in the Apple TV+ series Severance. Lachman was born in Kathmandu. Her mother is Tibetan and her father is an Australian of German ancestry. She grew up in Adelaide, South Australia. She moved to the United States in 2007 and lives in Los Angeles, California. She is married to Max Osinski and has one child. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Actors from Adelaide Category:Australian movie actors Category:Australian movie producers Category:Australian television actors Category:Actors from Kathmandu
